Use the standard library
This is how to select_words of s and n:
  Remember that words is []
  Remember that current is ""
  Do this s's length times:
    Remember that ch is item 0 in s
    Remember that s is item 1 in s
    When ch is " ", then:
      When current's length is n, then:
        Add words to current
      End when
      Remember that current is ""
    But, if not:
      Remember that current is "{current}{ch}"
    End when
    When s's length is 0, then:
      When current's length is n, then:
        Add words to current
      End when
    End when
  End do
  The answer is words
